POSITION PROFILE
Design and draft electrical assemblies using Zuken E3 Electrical;
Shipboard and Cabinet Design;
Cable Run Sheet and Cable Schedule;
Ensure drawings are produced in accordance with applicable drafting codes and standards;
Translate engineering sketches and mark-ups into properly documented drawings;
Draft electrical lock diagrams, schematics and cable assemblies to be compliant with task technical requirements;
Create Technical Product Specifications (TPS) to describe selected systems;
Oversee installation, operation, maintenance, and repair of electrical/electronic systems;
Work with manufacturing partners to introduce designs into production and solve related manufacturing issues;
Diagnose problems with existing designs, propose and test design modifications;
Assist with the Lead Engineer and/or Project Manager during design reviews;
Maintain currency of Electrical/Electronic design best practices, methodologies, initiatives.
Qualifications
QUALIFICATIONS
Bachelor of Engineering degree (Master’s is highly desirable);
At least 5 years of applicable engineering experience;
Experience in the Systems Engineering life cycle, including typical tools for requirements development (i.e. DOORS);
Strong English written and spoken skills.
